summary: An Ordinance appropriating the sum of Twenty-five ($25) Dollars out of the General Fund of the City of Seattle to pay the claim of Francis A. Coles for personal injuries received by him on the 25th day of August, 1915, at 10:15 P. M., while walking on the sidewalk on Third Avenue Northwest, between Leary Avenue and Fortieth Street West, in said city, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
